  <prompt>
Operator requirement (wave12 plan §2.1): "for the tools only need the 'Add To Do' (so just the checkmark — but in future we will add other tools so don't remove the three dot tool menu)". Update widget per-bullet tools: visible primary action = 'Add To Do' checkmark icon; secondary actions live behind the existing three-dot overflow menu. Preserve the three-dot menu component for future tool additions.
  </prompt>

  <role>
You are a PCF/React widget developer making a targeted UX change. Use Fluent UI v9 components (per ADR-006). Honor ADR-021 dark mode semantic tokens (no hardcoded colors).
  </role>

  <goal>
Each bullet in DailyBriefing widget displays an 'Add To Do' checkmark icon as primary visible tool; the three-dot overflow menu component is retained (for future tools) but contains only the existing actions today. UAT-verifiable: operator clicks checkmark → To Do creation flow invoked; clicks three dots → overflow menu opens.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    - Current DailyBriefing widget per-bullet rendering (R7 W11 deploy state)
    - 'Add To Do' tool wiring may or may not exist — verify; if missing, this task scopes the wire-up too
    - Three-dot overflow menu component must remain in component tree (operator emphasis on future extensibility)
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    - Per ADR-006: Fluent UI v9 only (no v8)
    - Per ADR-021: dark mode — use semantic tokens (`tokens.colorBrandForeground1`, etc.); NO hardcoded colors
    - Per CLAUDE.md §10 + §11: modification only; no new abstractions
    - MUST preserve three-dot overflow menu component (operator explicit)
    - MUST use Fluent UI v9 Checkmark icon (`@fluentui/react-icons` Checkmark24Regular or similar)
    - 'Add To Do' tool implementation may delegate to existing useDocumentActions hook OR similar pattern — investigate before building
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/wave12-mvp-completion-plan.md (§2.1 tools requirement)
