      - docs/guides/PCF-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md (mandatory version bumping)
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      - src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/components/** (per-bullet rendering components — locate)
      - src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/services/briefingService.ts (response shape)
      - Existing 'Add To Do' integration if shipped elsewhere (search codebase)
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <steps>
1. **Locate per-bullet rendering component + current tool layout** (15 min)
2. **Inspect existing three-dot overflow menu component** (10 min) — confirm structure
3. **Investigate 'Add To Do' tool wiring** (15-30 min):
   - Does a checkmark-click handler exist? If yes, lift to primary visible tool.
   - If no, identify the API + entity shape needed to create a sprk_todo from a bullet's context
4. **Update per-bullet UI** (30-60 min):
   - Primary visible: Fluent UI v9 Checkmark icon button (with aria-label "Add To Do")
   - Secondary: existing three-dot overflow menu (unchanged structurally)
   - Wire checkmark click to 'Add To Do' handler
5. **ADR-021 dark mode check** (15 min): use Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens; verify Light + Dark renders correctly
6. **Run widget unit tests** (10 min)
7. **Build widget** (5 min): `npm run build:prod`
8. **PCF deployment guide check** (10 min): bump version numbers in the 4 mandatory locations per docs/guides/PCF-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md if widget version is affected

  </steps>

  <tools>
    - Read / Grep / Glob
    - Edit (component update)
    - Bash (npm test, npm run build:prod)
    - TodoWrite
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    - Per-bullet component (M) — primary checkmark + preserved overflow
    - Version bump in 4 locations if applicable (per PCF-DEPLOYMENT-GUIDE.md)
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - [ ] 'Add To Do' checkmark icon visible as primary tool on each bullet
    - [ ] Three-dot overflow menu component preserved in component tree (for future tools)
    - [ ] Fluent UI v9 components used (Checkmark icon, IconButton)
    - [ ] ADR-021 dark mode: semantic tokens used; no hardcoded colors
    - [ ] Widget unit tests 0 new failures
